President Obama was briefed on the preparations for Tropical Storm Isaac, which was projected to become a Category One hurricane. FEMA has prepositioned resources along the Gulf Coast and set up Incident Support Bases in Florida and Alabama. Response teams have been deployed to Alabama, Florida, Louisiana, and Mississippi. The President directed FEMA to be prepared regardless of the storm's strength. He also had a call with the governors of Alabama, Louisiana, Mississippi, and the mayor of New Orleans to update them on the storm's track and FEMA's resources. The President approved an Emergency Declaration for Louisiana, providing federal funding for emergency activities related to the storm.